Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto half of a lightly oiled #baking tray{}. Grate the @Red Leicester{120%g} cheese.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

Bake the burgers on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

After a few mins, lay the @British Streaky Bacon{4} rashers on the other side of the #traying and bake until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

When the burgers have ~{4%minutes} left, sprinkle one third of the cheese onto each. Return to the oven for the remaining time to allow the cheese to melt.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @Macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, mix the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing together in a #large bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your dressing aside.

When the macaroni is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan.

Pour in the @Water for the Sauce{25%ml} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, then pop on medium-high heat. Bring to the boil, stirring continuously, then remove from the heat.

Vigorously stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g} and remaining cheese. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve the @Glazed Burger Bun{2}. Pop onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, slather the @Burger Sauce{45%g} over your bun bases and lids. Top each with a cheeseburger patty and bacon.

Toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} in the dressing and serve alongside your craft burgers with the mac & cheese. Enjoy!